name: Deadeye Dick Canyon
description:
Introduction

Approach

If you have a capable 4WD you might be able to drive past the official trailhead parking and shave 4 miles from the hike, though a sign at the main parking area states that to continue driving on the road is for official park operations only, so probably best not to attempt it.

Some may not be entirely comfortable with the approach from the bottom via the upper narrows of the North Fork of the Virgin River - in particular one 15 foot climb while heading up the approach canyon up an old, dead tree used to get up a vertical chute. The tree has lost many of the branches that would have assisted with the climb and is quite thin at the top. A spot from below and perhaps a rope assist from above after the first has made it up may be desired.

Descent

It is recommended to combine the descent with Mighty Mouse Canyon, which should add just 1h extra.

Exit

Background

properties.name: Bullochs Cabin
properties.description: Bulloch's Cabin. An old broke down cabin in a meadow just off the road on the south side.

properties.name: R1
properties.description: Rap 1 - Deadeye Dick Canyon. Anchored from a cairn style anchor and drops about 12 feet.

properties.name: R2
properties.description: Rap 2 - Deadeye Dick Canyon. Anchored from chokestones at the top of the drop and drops about 70 feet. The top half is in a convoluted twisty flute while the second half is down a slightly sloped wall. A short section of deep slot is below rap 2 quickly opening up to wide wash with lots of trees.

properties.name: R3
properties.description: Rap 3 - Deadeye Dick Canyon. Anchored from a tree LDC up on a ledge and raps down about 60 feet from the anchor. The upper part of rap 3 is in a twisted convoluted flute while the lower half is down a slightly sloped wall.

properties.name: R6
properties.description: Rap 6 - Deadeye Dick Canyon. Anchored from a log wedged in rock debris and drops about 120 feet down a VERY fun large flute with slick walls.

properties.name: R5
properties.description: Rap 5 is anchored from a chokestone and drops about 40 feet down a sloped crack.

properties.name: R4
properties.description: Rap 4 is anchored from some boulder debris on the RDC side and drops about 40 feet over two stages of boulder debris. Rap 4 is downclimbable LDC then RDC over the stages. Rap 5 is about 40 feet down canyon of rap 4 with a 12 foot stem style downclimb between.
